He looked about. The stands were almost full. This would be a well-attended Olympics, which meant greater strain on the contestants-or greater drive, perhaps, depending on the individual.\par
Why Olympics, he thought suddenly? He had never known. Why was bread called bread?\par
Once he had asked his father: \ldblquote Why do they call it Olympics, Dad?\rdblquote\par
