'All right. Draw the curtain back again.'\par
There were cautious footsteps through the dark, the rustle of Theremon's body against the curtain as he felt for the tassel, and then the triumphant roo-osh of the curtain slithering back. Red light flooded the room, and with a cry of joy Theremon looked up at the sun.\par
Sheerin wiped the moistness off his forehead with the back of a hand and said shakily, 'And that was just a dark room.'\par
'It can be stood,' said Theremon lightly.\par
'Yes, a dark room can. But were you at the Jonglor Centennial Exposition two years ago?'\par
'No, it so happens I never got around to it. Six thousand miles was just a bit too much to travel, even for the exposition.'\par
'Well, I was there. You remember hearing about the "Tunnel of Mystery" that broke all records in the amusement area -- for the first month or so, anyway?'\par
'Yes. Wasn't there some fuss about it?'\par
